"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-06-29-injured-miller-uibo-wont-defend-olympic-400m-crown\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"LOS ANGELES,\\u00a0United States\\u00a0(AFP) - Reigning Olympic 400m champion Shaunae Miller-Uibo will not defend her title at next month's Paris Games after suffering an injury, Bahamas athletics officials said.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaunae Miller-Uibo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\"}, {\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999994574376723, \"rank\": 5.341820542363023e-07, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Miller-Uibo, the 2016 and 2020 400m gold medallist who was chasing a hat-trick of Olympic titles in Paris, was aiming to seal qualification at the Bahamas trials.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999432608708, \"rank\": 5.67391668454809e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999994574376723, \"rank\": 5.341820542363023e-07, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the 30-year-old was injured ahead of the 400m final, meaning she will miss out on a place in her specialist event.\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's the darling of the sport and she will be missed.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, she's been dinged up with some injuries,\\\" Bahamas Association of Athletic Associations (BAAA) president Drumeco Archer told Eye Witness News Bahamas.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"score\": 0.9999682451156063, \"rank\": 3.1755891125607004e-05, \"text\": \"Archer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Archer said Miller-Uibo may yet compete in Paris as part of the Bahamas' 4x400m mixed relay squad, after helping the team qualify at the world relays earlier this year.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"score\": 0.9999682451156063, \"rank\": 3.1755891125607004e-05, \"text\": \"Archer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\"}, {\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999432608708, \"rank\": 5.67391668454809e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999994574376723, \"rank\": 5.341820542363023e-07, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's golden in our minds, and there could be some consideration for her running the relay depending on the time of her recovery,\\\" Archer said.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"score\": 0.9999682451156063, \"rank\": 3.1755891125607004e-05, \"text\": \"Archer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So we will wait and see what happens.\\\"\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Miller-Uibo has not run in an individual 400m this season.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Miller-Uibo's absence from the 400m in Paris makes her the latest Olympic athletics champion who will be unable to defend their title.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999432608708, \"rank\": 5.67391668454809e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's reigning 100m and 200m champion Elaine Thompson-Herah was ruled out of the Games through injury this week, while 800m champion Athing Mu fell during US trials in Eugene this week and failed to qualify.\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9218375778212318, \"rank\": 0.08476797051106008, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson-Herah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\"}